summary: An automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system reminding a traveler that their voucher for a trip to Santa Monica from November 13-15, 2019, is late. The trip's purpose was listed as 'U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interview'.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip Authorization
events.description: A DOJ employee's travel to Santa Monica for the purpose of conducting a witness interview for the U.S. v. Epstein case was authorized.

events.title: End of Witness Interview Trip
events.description: The authorized travel period for the DOJ employee to conduct a witness interview in Santa Monica for the U.S. v. Epstein case ended.

keyFacts: The document is a late voucher notification from the DOJ's internal travel system (E2Solutions).
The travel was for the specific purpose of a witness interview in the case 'U.S. v. Epstein'.
The trip occurred from November 13 to November 15, 2019, with a destination of Santa Monica.
The traveler's name is redacted in the provided text.
The document confirms ongoing investigative activity (witness interviews) in the Epstein case as of late 2019.
